-- South Korea’s Kospi Index Slumps 4.9% After Report of Kim Jong Il’s Death
-- B y   D a r r e n   B o e y
-- 2011-12-19T03:08:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/south-korea-s-kospi-index-slumps-4-9-after-report-of-kim-jong-il-s-death.html
South Korea ’s Kospi index slumped as
much as 4.9 percent after North Korean state television reported
that its leader  Kim Jong Il  has died.  The Kospi lost 4 percent to 1,766.82 as of 12:07 p.m. in
 Seoul . It earlier sank 4.9 percent to 1,750.60.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  